17
00:04:03,007 --> 00:04:04,565
<i>In view of the situation,</i>

18
00:04:04,887 --> 00:04:06,605
<i>I have decreed a state of siege</i>

19
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:08,405
<i>for the entire country,</i>

20
00:04:08,727 --> 00:04:10,718
<i>and informed Congress of it.</i>

21
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,765
<i>Our country is going through</i>
<i>a difficult period...</i>

22
00:04:45,247 --> 00:04:47,078
Kick 'em all out!

23
00:04:47,247 --> 00:04:49,363
Every one of them!

24
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:56,725
The government must resign

25
00:04:56,927 --> 00:04:59,760
Together, we'll never be defeated!

26
00:05:06,927 --> 00:05:08,758
<i>After many years</i>

27
00:05:09,047 --> 00:05:11,641
<i>of apathy in the country,</i>

28
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,239
<i>the insurrection exploded.</i>

29
00:05:16,007 --> 00:05:18,999
<i>This spontaneous revolt</i>
<i>of "faceless" people</i>

30
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:21,761
<i>meant saucepans were being banged</i>

31
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:23,559
<i>in every neighborhood,</i>

32
00:05:23,887 --> 00:05:26,924
<i>all the way</i>
<i>to the city's vital centers.</i>

33
00:05:28,207 --> 00:05:31,597
People took to the streets,

34
00:05:31,807 --> 00:05:33,445
without getting any orders.

35
00:05:33,607 --> 00:05:36,519
I've been out of work
for six weeks,

36
00:05:36,687 --> 00:05:38,996
and I've slaved away
my whole life.

37
00:05:39,207 --> 00:05:41,084
I don't want a state of siege,

38
00:05:41,247 --> 00:05:45,035
or to be a pawn
of the International Monetary Fund.

39
00:05:45,247 --> 00:05:47,158
It's an outdated economic model.

40
00:05:47,327 --> 00:05:50,603
De la Rúa must resign,
and all the swindlers with him.

41
