"In glory we shall die!"

44
00:06:45,927 --> 00:06:48,566
"In glory we shall die!"

45
00:06:56,567 --> 00:07:01,118
"This square belongs to the Mothers,

46
00:07:01,807 --> 00:07:03,525
"not to cowardly others!"

47
00:07:06,647 --> 00:07:08,444
"This square belongs to the Mothers,

48
00:07:08,607 --> 00:07:10,359
"not to cowardly others!"

49
00:07:34,647 --> 00:07:35,841
You bastards!

50
00:07:39,047 --> 00:07:42,005
We're not in a dictatorship anymore!

51
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,964
Bunch of idiots!

52
00:07:44,127 --> 00:07:46,004
Armed baboons!

53
00:07:55,727 --> 00:07:57,797
Who ordered you out?

54
00:07:58,007 --> 00:07:59,645
Can you kill a woman?

55
00:07:59,807 --> 00:08:03,402
Can you kill a whole nation
because you're ordered to?

56
00:08:03,727 --> 00:08:06,400
Repression fails to empty
the Plaza de Mayo

57
00:08:44,167 --> 00:08:47,443
Hundreds of citizens
rally to the movement

58
00:08:47,687 --> 00:08:50,485
"The people won't clear out!"

59
00:08:59,607 --> 00:09:01,882
<i>And the people don't clear out.</i>

60
00:09:02,767 --> 00:09:05,486
<i>They're workers, housewives,</i>

61
00:09:05,927 --> 00:09:08,999
<i>employees, pensioners, students,</i>

62
00:09:09,727 --> 00:09:12,685
<i>the heirs of those who,</i>
<i>for decades,</i>

63
00:09:13,127 --> 00:09:16,802
<i>defied the dictatorships</i>
<i>and the persecutions,</i>

64
00:09:17,207 --> 00:09:19,323
<i>put up with</i>
<i>the policies of austerity,</i>

65
00:09:19,487 --> 00:09:21,000
<i>and were betrayed</i>

66
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:23,119
<i>by democracy.</i>

67
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:29,565
<i>What happened in Argentina?</i>

68
00:09:31,127 --> 00:09:34,483
<i>How was it possible</i>
<i>that in so rich a country</i>

69
00:09:35,087 --> 00:09:37,726
<i>so many people were hungry?</i>

70
00:09:41,727 --> 00:09:46,403
<i>The country had been ransacked</i>
<i>by a new form of aggression,</i>

71
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:51,204
<i>committed in time of peace</i>
<i>and in a democracy.</i>

72
00:09:51,927 --> 00:09:55,078
<i>A daily and silent violence</i>

73
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:00,797
<i>that caused</i>
<i>greater social disruption,</i>

74
00:10:03,887 --> 00:10:06,242
<i>more emigration and death,</i>

75
00:10:06,807 --> 00:10:09,367
<i>than the terrorism</i>
<i>of the dictatorship</i>

76
00:10:09,527 --> 00:10:11,836
<i>and the Falkland Islands war.</i>

77
00:10:22,367 --> 00:10:26,121
THE NEVER-ENDING DEBT

78
00:10:29,447 --> 00:10:32,837
<i>Ever since Independence,</i>
<i>almost 200 years ago,</i>

79
00:10:33,207 --> 00:10:36,119
<i>Argentina's foreign debt</i>
<i>has been a source</i>

80
00:10:36,287 --> 00:10:39,199
<i>of impoverishment and corruption</i>

81
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:42,245
<i>and the biggest scandals.</i>

82
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:49,836
<i>Since the first loan</i>
<i>negotiated by Rivadavia in 1824</i>

83
00:10:50,447 --> 00:10:53,120
<i>with the British bank</i>
<i>Baring Brothers,</i>

84
00:10:54,287 --> 00:10:58,599
<i>the debt was used</i>
<i>to enrich Argentinean financiers,</i>

85
00:10:59,687 --> 00:11:01,359
<i>to control the finances</i>

86
00:11:01,527 --> 00:11:04,837
<i>and empty the country</i>
<i>of its wealth.</i>

87
00:11:06,487 --> 00:11:11,163
<i>This foreign debt always</i>
<i>went hand in hand with big business,</i>

88
00:11:11,327 --> 00:11:15,115
<i>and with the complicity</i>
<i>of nearly every government,</i>

89
00:11:15,527 --> 00:11:20,043
<i>from Miter and Quintana,</i>
<i>to Menem and De la Rúa.</i>

90
00:11:25,247 --> 00:11:29,923
<i>The policy of indebtedness</i>
<i>gave rise in Argentina</i>

91
00:11:30,087 --> 00:11:33,875
<i>to generations</i>
<i>of technocrats and bureaucrats,</i>

92
00:11:34,127 --> 00:11:39,155
<i>who favored banks</i>
<i>and international corporations</i>

93
00:11:39,327 --> 00:11:41,238
<i>over their own country.</i>

94
00:11:43,847 --> 00:11:47,840
<i>Educated at Harvard, Chicago,</i>
<i>Oxford or Buenos Aires,</i>

95
00:11:48,247 --> 00:11:52,035
<i>their portraits hang</i>
<i>in the official galleries.</i>

96
00:11:54,247 --> 00:11:58,479
<i>There you can see</i>
<i>19th century lobbyists,</i>

97
00:11:58,807 --> 00:12:01,321
<i>like Manual García and Beláustegui,</i>

98
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:05,162
<i>or the latest heads</i>
<i>of the public banking system,</i>

99
00:12:05,407 --> 00:12:08,479
<i>Pedro Pou,</i>
<i>Macarrone and Colombo,</i>

100
00:12:10,447 --> 00:12:12,881
<i>administrators of a debt</i>

101
00:12:13,207 --> 00:12:16,005
<i>that was born in the 1970s</i>

102
00:12:16,327 --> 00:12:18,443
<i>under the military dictatorship.</i>

103
00:12:22,487 --> 00:12:25,126
<i>We have turned the page</i>

104
00:12:25,487 --> 00:12:29,162
<i>of government interventionism...</i>

105
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:32,200
<i>The present debt</i>

106
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:34,198
<i>was the illegitimate offspring</i>

107
00:12:34,447 --> 00:12:36,517
<i>of the military dictatorship.</i>

108
00:12:37,807 --> 00:12:42,119
<i>Even though the Courts</i>
<i>demonstrated its fraudulent origins,</i>

109
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:46,596
<i>the pressure of the Establishment</i>
<i>won the day.</i>

110
00:12:49,327 --> 00:12:50,919
<i>From then on,</i>

111
00:12:51,207 --> 00:12:53,562
<i>it dictated national policies</i>

112
00:12:53,727 --> 00:12:56,366
<i>and depleted the public heritage.</i>

113
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:02,923
<i>All this is perfectly symbolized</i>

114
00:13:03,247 --> 00:13:07,479
<i>by the statue of George Canning,</i>
<i>an advocate of colonial policies,</i>

115
00:13:08,247 --> 00:13:13,002
<i>that was donated</i>
<i>by the British Government in 1857,</i>

116
00:13:13,847 --> 00:13:17,237
<i>in recognition of the debt.</i>

