00:49:20,407 --> 00:49:23,717
<i>with the U.S. Secretary</i>
<i>of the Treasury, Nicholas Brady,</i>

699
00:49:23,887 --> 00:49:27,038
<i>exchanging this debt</i>
<i>against our national heritage,</i>

700
00:49:27,247 --> 00:49:29,283
<i>for a bargain price.</i>

701
00:49:30,647 --> 00:49:34,640
<i>State enterprises are purchased,</i>
<i>with national bonds</i>

702
00:49:34,807 --> 00:49:38,595
<i>pegged at 15% of their face value,</i>

703
00:49:38,967 --> 00:49:41,765
<i>but redeemable at 100%.</i>

704
00:49:43,847 --> 00:49:46,122
<i>This agreement made the country lose</i>

705
00:49:46,287 --> 00:49:49,120
<i>more that 30 billion dollars.</i>

706
00:49:49,887 --> 00:49:52,481
PRIVATIZATIONS

707
00:49:55,407 --> 00:49:57,398
<i>The Argentine government</i>

708
00:49:58,287 --> 00:50:00,005
<i>achieved tonight</i>

709
00:50:00,207 --> 00:50:03,040
<i>seven fundamental privatizations,</i>

710
00:50:03,607 --> 00:50:06,724
<i>in seven strategic sectors</i>
<i>for the country.</i>

711
00:50:06,887 --> 00:50:10,516
<i>We'll move on</i>
<i>to the privatization of TV,</i>

712
00:50:10,767 --> 00:50:12,485
<i>of phone companies,</i>

713
00:50:12,727 --> 00:50:15,366
<i>of a forthcoming tollbooth system,</i>

714
00:50:15,607 --> 00:50:19,885
<i>of forthcoming road and railway</i>
<i>concessions,</i>

715
00:50:20,167 --> 00:50:22,840
<i>as well as</i>
<i>the privatization of radio,</i>

716
00:50:23,007 --> 00:50:24,565
<i>without forgetting, of course,</i>

717
00:50:24,927 --> 00:50:28,283
<i>the privatization</i>
<i>of the national airline.</i>

718
00:50:28,687 --> 00:50:32,202
<i>We've elaborated</i>
<i>our Ten Commandments,</i>

719
00:50:32,367 --> 00:50:35,598
<i>the Menemist Ten Commandments</i>
<i>for the Reform of the State.</i>

720
00:50:35,767 --> 00:50:37,086
<i>Commandment number 1,</i>

721
00:50:37,247 --> 00:50:39,602
<i>Menem doesn't know it yet,</i>

722
00:50:39,807 --> 00:50:43,163
<i>is taken from one of his speeches:</i>

723
00:50:43,567 --> 00:50:47,003
<i>"Nothing belonging to the State</i>
<i>will remain in its hands."</i>

724
00:50:53,087 --> 00:50:54,805
<i>Nothing was spared.</i>

725
00:50:56,167 --> 00:50:59,716
<i>No matter what it was,</i>
<i>or how much it cost,</i>

726
00:50:59,927 --> 00:51:02,839
<i>or how and why it was sold.</i>

727
00:51:11,527 --> 00:51:14,325
<i>Cued by the methods</i>
<i>of other centuries,</i>

728
00:51:14,647 --> 00:51:17,115
<i>these privatizations</i>

729
00:51:17,327 --> 00:51:21,445
<i>were an extension</i>
<i>of the old colonial expropriations.</i>

730
00:51:22,207 --> 00:51:25,244
<i>Once, the Potosí was robbed</i>
<i>of its silver and gold.</i>

731
00:51:25,767 --> 00:51:30,045
<i>Now oil, water,</i>
<i>and communications are stolen.</i>

732
00:51:31,327 --> 00:51:35,718
<i>The foreign companies</i>
<i>did in our country</i>

733
00:51:35,887 --> 00:51:39,880
<i>what they couldn't do</i>
<i>in their own countries.</i>

734
00:51:41,087 --> 00:51:42,918
Non-execution of works

735
00:51:43,527 --> 00:51:46,325
They were exonerated

736
00:51:46,487 --> 00:51:47,681
for the non-execution of works.

737
00:51:47,847 --> 00:51:50,122
Rates were raised

738
00:51:50,327 --> 00:51:54,240
to make the users
pay for the investments.

739
00:51:54,407 --> 00:51:56,875
No new capital was needed.

740
00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:59,642
The more you risk,
the more you earn.

741
00:51:59,807 --> 00:52:04,164
In Argentina, no risks
yielded huge profits.

742
00:52:04,367 --> 00:52:06,801
Outstanding profitability

743
00:52:08,367 --> 00:52:12,485
They either doubled or tripled
the rates in dollars.

744
00:52:13,087 --> 00:52:16,682
26 privatized concerns,
13% of the total number,

745
00:52:16,847 --> 00:52:19,042
pocketed 60% of the income.

746
00:52:19,487 --> 00:52:21,523
26 privatized concerns
60% of the income

747
00:52:22,527 --> 00:52:23,880
France Telecom in Argentina

748
00:52:24,047 --> 00:52:27,278
had a profitability of 15%

749
00:52:27,447 --> 00:52:29,244
and Telefónica of 16%,

750
00:52:29,407 --> 00:52:32,126
whereas the ten biggest
international operators

751
00:52:32,287 --> 00:52:35,279
only average
a profitability of 5,4%.

752
00:52:35,647 --> 00:52:37,763
5% worldwide
16% in Argentina

753
00:52:38,367 --> 00:52:43,122
These concerns are private here,
and public in their own countries.

754
00:52:43,407 --> 00:52:45,125
Stripping

755
00:52:46,087 --> 00:52:49,796
<i>The Argentinean enterprises</i>
<i>were sold without debts.</i>

756
00:52:49,967 --> 00:52:53,084
<i>The State took care</i>
<i>of the 150000 layoffs</i>

757
00:52:53,247 --> 00:52:55,807
<i>required by the purchasers.</i>

758
00:52:56,407 --> 00:53:00,116
<i>The main investors</i>
<i>were Spanish and French:</i>

759
00:53:00,327 --> 00:53:03,603
<i>The profitable ENTEL was sold</i>
<i>for a fifth of its value</i>

760
00:53:03,767 --> 00:53:06,076
<i>to Telefônica and France Telecom,</i>

761
00:53:06,247 --> 00:53:09,922
<i>who saddled it</i>
<i>with a 6 billion dollar debt.</i>

762
00:53:11,287 --> 00:53:15,997
<i>Aerolíneas Argentinas</i>
<i>was profitable and owned 37 planes.</i>

763
00:53:16,967 --> 00:53:20,403
<i>The Spanish line Iberia mortgaged</i>
<i>them to purchase the business,</i>

764
00:53:20,567 --> 00:53:23,240
<i>and stripped it of all its assets.</i>

765
00:53:25,967 --> 00:53:29,437
<i>The State water utility was taken</i>
<i>over by a European syndicate</i>

766
00:53:29,607 --> 00:53:32,804
<i>headed by Suez and Vivendi.</i>

767
00:53:33,247 --> 00:53:35,966
<i>After making it owe</i>
<i>8 times its assets,</i>

768
00:53:36,127 --> 00:53:38,721
<i>huge profits were made,</i>

769
00:53:38,887 --> 00:53:41,799
<i>but the works agreed to</i>
<i>were not completed.</i>

770
00:53:42,167 --> 00:53:45,842
<i>800000 people were left</i>
<i>without drinking water,</i>

771
00:53:46,207 --> 00:53:48,767
<i>and a million people</i>
<i>had no sewers.</i>

772
00:53:54,927 --> 00:53:57,236
<i>The worse case is probably</i>

773
00:53:57,527 --> 00:54:00,246
<i>the dislocation of the railroads</i>

774
00:54:01,007 --> 00:54:05,205
<i>that dealt a fatal blow</i>
<i>to regional economies.</i>

775
00:54:05,767 --> 00:54:08,406
<i>Thousands of families had to move.</i>

776
00:54:10,567 --> 00:54:13,718
<i>36000km of tracks existed,</i>

777
00:54:14,207 --> 00:54:16,163
<i>now only 8000 remain.</i>

778
00:54:17,447 --> 00:54:20,086
<i>There were 95000 jobs,</i>

779
00:54:20,767 --> 00:54:22,644
<i>now only 15000 are left.</i>

780
00:54:23,927 --> 00:54:27,886
<i>Ten years later, the State</i>
<i>pays out more and more subsidies,</i>

781
00:54:28,047 --> 00:54:29,765
<i>and now owes the World Bank</i>

782
00:54:29,927 --> 00:54:34,079
<i>700 million dollars</i>
<i>borrowed to pay for the layoffs,</i>

783
00:54:34,967 --> 00:54:38,277
<i>and another 700 million</i>
<i>in interest...</i>

784
00:54:39,407 --> 00:54:43,241
<i>Just to suppress 80000 jobs!</i>

785
00:54:48,247 --> 00:54:50,124
Billions in subsidies

786
00:54:51,367 --> 00:54:53,358
Privatizations were supposed

787
00:54:53,527 --> 00:54:55,245
to end the payment of subsidies

788
00:54:55,447 --> 00:54:58,803
that supposedly led
to the public deficit.

789
00:54:59,727 --> 00:55:03,959
The irony today, is that
most of the privatized companies,

790
00:55:04,447 --> 00:55:06,119
are subsidized.

791
00:55:06,607 --> 00:55:10,077
Just for
the national highway system,

792
00:55:10,247 --> 00:55:12,681
the subsidy was
1,1 billion dollars.

793
00:55:13,127 --> 00:55:16,119
And as the 980 million
for acquiring them weren't paid,

794
00:55:16,287 --> 00:55:18,357
they stole a total
of 2 billion dollars!

795
00:55:18,887 --> 00:55:20,798
They never paid the fee

796
00:55:21,087 --> 00:55:22,645
You have to pay a fee

797
00:55:22,807 --> 00:55:26,482
to use public property
belonging to a country.

798
00:55:26,647 --> 00:55:27,841
They never paid it.

799
00:55:28,047 --> 00:55:29,400
- Who didn't pay?
- No one.

800
00:55:29,567 --> 00:55:31,922
Not for the roads,
the postal system, the airports...

801
00:55:32,527 --> 00:55:34,324
Impunity

802
00:55:34,567 --> 00:55:37,764
Legal protection always favored

803
00:55:37,927 --> 00:55:39,804
the conglomerates.

804
00:55:40,007 --> 00:55:43,124
No one negotiated for the consumers.

805
00:55:43,807 --> 00:55:48,278
Why such impunity?

806
00:55:49,127 --> 00:55:50,719
Politics.

807
00:55:51,807 --> 00:55:54,082
Big business
and political scheming.

808
00:55:54,407 --> 00:55:56,602
The big conglomerates

809
00:55:58,247 --> 00:56:02,843
<i>Privatizations were planned in</i>
<i>the interest in the big conglomerates.</i>

810
00:56:03,047 --> 00:56:08,485
<i>They were the ones who financed</i>
<i>all the election campaigns,</i>

811
00:56:08,647 --> 00:56:10,365
<i>all the governments,</i>

812
00:56:10,527 --> 00:56:12,518
<i>all the coups d'état,</i>

813
00:56:12,687 --> 00:56:16,316
<i>all the major public-works</i>
<i>undertakings.</i>

814
00:56:20,367 --> 00:56:23,916
<i>No other sector</i>
<i>benefited from such privileges:</i>

815
00:56:24,207 --> 00:56:27,165
<i>Protected markets,</i>
<i>astronomical subsidies,</i>

816
00:56:27,807 --> 00:56:31,117
<i>fiscal advantages,</i>
<i>rate-overcharging,</i>

817
00:56:31,287 --> 00:56:34,359
<i>exoneration of penalties</i>
<i>for non-performance of work,</i>

818
00:56:34,527 --> 00:56:36,199
<i>extensions of concessions,</i>

819
00:56:36,367 --> 00:56:39,643
<i>and conversion into pesos</i>
<i>of debts in dollars.</i>

820
00:56:41,367 --> 00:56:45,724
<i>They failed to honor</i>
<i>their contracts with the State,</i>

821
00:56:45,887 --> 00:56:49,323
<i>swindled it</i>
<i>and then sued it for damages.</i>

822
00:56:50,807 --> 00:56:52,035
<i>Among these were:</i>

823
00:56:52,807 --> 00:56:55,116
<i>Macri's Socma and Sideco,</i>

824
00:56:55,327 --> 00:56:57,557
<i>Bulgheroni's Bridas,</i>

825
00:56:57,767 --> 00:57:00,235
<i>Fortabat's Loma Negra,</i>

826
00:57:00,447 --> 00:57:02,722
<i>Pérez Companc's Pecom,</i>

827
00:57:02,927 --> 00:57:04,804
<i>Rocca's Techint,</i>

828
00:57:05,047 --> 00:57:08,801
<i>Benito Roggio, Pescarmona,</i>
<i>and others.</i>

829
00:57:18,167 --> 00:57:20,635
<i>Unemployment</i>
<i>is spreading like a plague,</i>

830
00:57:20,807 --> 00:57:23,446
<i>contaminating the whole society.</i>

831
00:57:23,607 --> 00:57:28,123
<i>The lines of dole seekers</i>
<i>get longer everywhere.</i>

832
00:57:28,847 --> 00:57:32,726
<i>Unemployment has gone from 11%</i>
<i>to more than 20%,</i>

833
00:57:32,887 --> 00:57:35,276
<i>not counting the temps.</i>

834
00:57:35,527 --> 00:57:37,995
What's the situation
of the workers?

835
00:57:38,167 --> 00:57:40,078
They've lost their salaries,

836
00:57:40,247 --> 00:57:42,158
their social benefits,

837
00:57:42,327 --> 00:57:44,841
their unemployment insurance,

838
00:57:45,007 --> 00:57:48,602
their accident
and sickness coverage.

839
00:57:48,767 --> 00:57:52,680
More than half of them
are moonlighting,

840
00:57:52,847 --> 00:57:55,202
a social situation

841
00:57:55,367 --> 00:57:58,086
that only prevails in the most
under-developed countries.

842
00:57:58,247 --> 00:58:02,126
People don't dare resist,
they fear layoffs,

843
00:58:02,647 --> 00:58:04,319
and that the next day

844
00:58:04,487 --> 00:58:07,559
there may be no solution at all.

845
00:58:07,727 --> 00:58:10,400
So they agree to salary cuts,

846
00:58:10,567 --> 00:58:12,797
deteriorating work conditions,

847
00:58:12,967 --> 00:58:15,845
working in unsanitary surroundings.

848
00:58:16,127 --> 00:58:18,880
Losing your job
means ending in a void,

849
00:58:19,047 --> 00:58:21,925
joining an army of beggars,

850
00:58:22,127 --> 00:58:24,687
the army of the excluded.

851
00:58:25,607 --> 00:58:29,520
It leads to depression,
to anxiety...

852
00:58:30,767 --> 00:58:32,246
<i>In the Latin-American country</i>

853
00:58:32,407 --> 00:58:35,956
<i>where social rights</i>
<i>were once most advanced,</i>

854
00:58:36,127 --> 00:58:38,118
<i>thousands of destitute people</i>

855
00:58:38,327 --> 00:58:41,285
<i>flock to the church</i>
<i>of San Cayetano,</i>

856
00:58:41,447 --> 00:58:43,403
<i>patron saint of work,</i>

857
00:58:43,567 --> 00:58:45,478
<i>asking for help.</i>

858
00:58:48,407 --> 00:58:51,444
THE LIQUIDATION OF OIL

859
00:58:53,287 --> 00:58:55,642
Argentina is a unique case

860
00:58:55,807 --> 00:58:57,320
in the world and in Latin America.

861
00:58:57,687 --> 00:59:00,759
No other country gave up

862
00:59:00,927 --> 00:59:04,158
its gas and oil
without losing a war.

863
00:59:04,687 --> 00:59:08,077
The country was truly betrayed

864
00:59:09,007 --> 00:59:10,804
by the ruling class.

865
00:59:10,967 --> 00:59:13,925
Mexico, Brazil and Venezuela

866
00:59:14,087 --> 00:59:16,521
never privatized their oil.

867
00:59:16,687 --> 00:59:20,566
Why was the sale of YPF
such an atrocity?

868
00:59:20,727 --> 00:59:25,039
Because of the role that YPF played

869
00:59:25,207 --> 00:59:26,686
in the country,

870
00:59:26,887 --> 00:59:29,685
and in the world oil-market.

871
00:59:29,887 --> 00:59:32,082
You have to remember
that when Mosconi

872
00:59:32,247 --> 00:59:35,842
created YPF, the first
State enterprise in the world,

873
00:59:36,007 --> 00:59:39,636
oil was considered
to be very strategic,

874
00:59:39,807 --> 00:59:43,846
and the sale of fuel
to be of national interest.

875
00:59:44,007 --> 00:59:46,123
If the international price rose,

876
00:59:46,287 --> 00:59:49,324
YPF kept the price low,

877
00:59:49,487 --> 00:59:52,684
according to its costs
and not the market price.

878
00:59:53,127 --> 00:59:57,518
<i>YPF was created in 1923</i>

879
00:59:57,687 --> 01:00:00,360
<i>on orders of General Mosconi.</i>

880
01:00:01,727 --> 01:00:06,005
<i>In 1907, oil had been discovered</i>
<i>in Patagonia.</i>

881
01:00:08,487 --> 01:00:10,045
<i>In spite of its detractors,</i>

882
01:00:10,807 --> 01:00:13,446
<i>the oil company was developed</i>

883
01:00:13,607 --> 01:00:16,121
<i>without the need for foreign funds,</i>

884
01:00:16,287 --> 01:00:19,040
<i>and became a model</i>
<i>for Latin America.</i>

885
01:00:21,567 --> 01:00:24,365
<i>It expanded so rapidly</i>

886
01:00:24,527 --> 01:00:28,042
<i>that it earned as much for the country</i>
<i>as the province of Buenos Aires.</i>

887
01:00:28,207 --> 01:00:32,917
<i>Its reserves were estimated</i>
<i>to be worth 200 billion dollars.</i>

888
01:00:37,367 --> 01:00:42,885
To privatize it, they had
to commit many irregularities.

889
01:00:43,367 --> 01:00:46,006
Actually, if the law was applied,

890
01:00:46,167 --> 01:00:48,635
most private concessions
would be invalid.

891
01:00:48,967 --> 01:00:52,846
Argentina could soon rebuild
its national oil company,

892
01:00:53,207 --> 01:00:56,199
if it had true political motivation.

893
01:00:58,687 --> 01:01:00,359
The strategic reserves,

894
01:01:00,567 --> 01:01:02,205
where the greatest sums
were invested,

895
01:01:02,367 --> 01:01:05,086
were awarded for 25 years,

896
01:01:05,247 --> 01:01:08,159
for a price equivalent
to 9 months of production.

897
01:01:08,927 --> 01:01:11,395
They were so poorly sold

898
01:01:11,567 --> 01:01:15,162
that Menem
had to deal with it personally.

899
01:01:15,967 --> 01:01:19,084
$19 for shares
that were worth $38...

900
01:01:19,247 --> 01:01:22,876
350 million shares at $19,
is a gigantic swindle.

901
01:01:23,567 --> 01:01:27,446
They even hired
the McKinley company

902
01:01:27,607 --> 01:01:30,360
to underestimate the reserves.

903
01:01:30,527 --> 01:01:35,123
A year later, the reserves reappeared
in the accounts at their real value.

904
01:01:35,327 --> 01:01:37,636
So they sold, say,
a reserve for 100,

905
01:01:37,807 --> 01:01:40,765
when it was worth 140.

906
01:01:41,247 --> 01:01:43,477
A cartel of four multinationals

907
01:01:43,647 --> 01:01:48,437
applied the highest rates
on earth to us

908
01:01:48,607 --> 01:01:51,360
and paid the lowest royalties.

909
01:01:51,527 --> 01:01:55,076
Who checks up?
They pump as much they want?

910
01:01:55,247 --> 01:01:57,681
They make a declaration
under oath.

911
01:01:57,847 --> 01:01:58,643
Meaning?

912
01:01:58,807 --> 01:02:00,240
By a declaration under oath,

913
01:02:00,407 --> 01:02:04,559
informing the Argentineans
how much they pumped.

914
01:02:04,767 --> 01:02:09,795
The reserves, the facilities,
were sold for a pittance.

915
01:02:10,367 --> 01:02:11,766
They didn't have to do anything.

916
01:02:11,927 --> 01:02:15,761
The site was there,
with the staff and the facilities,

917
01:02:15,927 --> 01:02:20,478
and everything
needed to transport the oil.

918
01:02:21,007 --> 01:02:26,684
A high quality infrastructure
that belonged to YPF.

919
01:02:27,207 --> 01:02:31,359
They didn't have to do anything,
because a concern like YPF

920
01:02:31,527 --> 01:02:33,677
had completely planned

921
01:02:33,887 --> 01:02:36,924
its future 20 years ahead.

922
01:02:37,087 --> 01:02:38,805
Now they were exploiting it,

923
01:02:38,967 --> 01:02:41,720
benefiting
from their State acquisitions,

924
01:02:41,887 --> 01:02:45,641
in terms of oil
and gas infrastructures.

925
01:02:45,807 --> 01:02:48,037
That's the reality of Argentina.

926
01:02:51,087 --> 01:02:54,966
<i>You can't understand</i>
<i>industrial development in Argentina</i>

927
01:02:55,367 --> 01:02:56,720
<i>and Patagonia,</i>

928
01:02:56,887 --> 01:02:59,355
<i>without knowing about YPF.</i>

929
01:02:59,927 --> 01:03:01,918
<i>It had developed pipelines,</i>

930
01:03:02,487 --> 01:03:05,206
<i>steel plants, roads and factories,</i>

931
01:03:05,847 --> 01:03:08,725
<i>and given birth to dozens of towns,</i>

932
01:03:08,887 --> 01:03:12,277
<i>geared to the social needs</i>
<i>of their inhabitants.</i>

933
01:03:13,207 --> 01:03:15,004
<i>In particular:</i>

934
01:03:15,487 --> 01:03:18,320
<i>Comodoro Rivadavia, Caleta Olivia,</i>

935
01:03:18,567 --> 01:03:21,206
<i>Cutral-Cô and Plaza Huincul,</i>

936
01:03:21,447 --> 01:03:24,120
<i>which was the first oil-town</i>

937
01:03:24,727 --> 01:03:26,922
<i>in the province of Neuquén.</i>

938
01:03:29,487 --> 01:03:32,559
All these empty,
walled up buildings,

939
01:03:32,767 --> 01:03:34,485
lying neglected,

940
01:03:34,687 --> 01:03:36,279
were Camp 1,

941
01:03:36,487 --> 01:03:38,318
the administration block,

942
01:03:38,527 --> 01:03:40,279
the heart of YPF.

943
01:03:40,767 --> 01:03:42,883
When it was privatized,

944
01:03:43,047 --> 01:03:46,278
people had to leave
to look for another livelihood.

945
01:03:46,447 --> 01:03:49,439
They abandoned their homes,

946
01:03:49,607 --> 01:03:51,802
in search of new horizons.

947
01:03:52,567 --> 01:03:54,364
Were you adequately paid?

948
01:03:54,567 --> 01:03:57,286
The wages? No problem...

949
01:03:58,247 --> 01:04:02,684
Here, no one was ever needy.

950
01:04:03,727 --> 01:04:06,321
What happened was a crime,
a murder.

951
01:04:06,487 --> 01:04:10,116
No one ever imagined
this could happen.

952
01:04:12,487 --> 01:04:17,083
Privatizations were done
almost without inventories.

953
01:04:17,287 --> 01:04:20,996
YPF left behind lots of things
that disappeared.

954
01:04:21,247 --> 01:04:23,477
Large motors, for instance...

955
01:04:23,647 --> 01:04:27,117
Vehicles, new equipment,

956
01:04:27,487 --> 01:04:30,524
drilling bits, tools, clothing...

957
01:04:30,927 --> 01:04:35,205
No track was kept of many items
that were never found.

958
01:04:36,087 --> 01:04:38,157
You can dismantle a hangar

959
01:04:38,367 --> 01:04:40,483
without anyone asking questions.

960
01:04:40,687 --> 01:04:42,405
This is what's left of PEXSE,

961
01:04:42,567 --> 01:04:45,604
a company created
by the oil-workers union SUPE

962
01:04:45,767 --> 01:04:50,397
to make the workers believe
they could be entrepreneurs.

963
01:04:50,927 --> 01:04:54,522
The company went bankrupt,
owing us money.

964
01:04:55,367 --> 01:04:58,677
The SUPE executives
were in on the fraud.

965
01:04:58,847 --> 01:05:02,635
They knew very well
that YPF would be dismantled.

966
01:05:08,407 --> 01:05:11,160
People accepted
$40 or $50000 dollars

967
01:05:11,327 --> 01:05:13,238
and agreed to get fired.

968
01:05:13,407 --> 01:05:16,877
They were paid to take
a training course in pastry-making,

969
01:05:17,127 --> 01:05:21,200
data processing, anything,
for a year.

970
01:05:21,927 --> 01:05:26,762
They accepted privatization
and layoffs without a struggle

971
01:05:26,927 --> 01:05:28,599
because they had money
in their pockets.

972
01:05:28,767 --> 01:05:30,837
Then they spent this money,

973
01:05:31,007 --> 01:05:35,080
bought a car, enlarged their home,
started a business.

974
01:05:35,407 --> 01:05:37,079
Did it create many unemployed?

975
01:05:37,247 --> 01:05:40,523
Between 5000 and 7000,
maybe more.

976
01:05:40,687 --> 01:05:44,123
There are no reliable figures,

977
01:05:44,567 --> 01:05:46,842
but it's known to be
in the thousands.

978
01:05:47,007 --> 01:05:50,204
There were thousands
of us semi-employed,

979
01:05:50,367 --> 01:05:52,244
trying to get by.

980
01:05:55,847 --> 01:05:59,362
<i>The unemployed</i>
<i>weren't all from YPF.</i>

981
01:06:01,287 --> 01:06:03,118
<i>Thousands of others came</i>

982
01:06:03,407 --> 01:06:05,363
<i>from the factories and businesses</i>

983
01:06:05,527 --> 01:06:07,199
<i>that also had to close.</i>

984
01:06:07,767 --> 01:06:09,359
<i>Some years later,</i>

985
01:06:10,167 --> 01:06:12,203
<i>during the winter of 1996,</i>

986
01:06:12,607 --> 01:06:16,156
<i>there was a revolt in Cutral-Cô.</i>

987
01:06:18,047 --> 01:06:19,765
<i>We're starving!</i>

988
01:06:19,967 --> 01:06:23,516
<i>We give them gas,</i>
<i>oil, electricity!</i>

989
01:06:23,927 --> 01:06:26,521
<i>Unable to find work,</i>

990
01:06:27,007 --> 01:06:31,080
<i>thousands of unemployed</i>
<i>blocked the main highway</i>

991
01:06:31,247 --> 01:06:33,522
<i>for days and nights,</i>

992
01:06:33,687 --> 01:06:36,599
<i>in freezing temperatures,</i>

993
01:06:37,247 --> 01:06:40,876
<i>and facing</i>
<i>the charges of the state police.</i>

994
01:06:51,047 --> 01:06:52,400
<i>That single victory</i>

995
01:06:53,167 --> 01:06:55,886
<i>created the "piquetero" movement</i>

996
01:06:56,047 --> 01:06:58,561
<i>with its "roadblocks".</i>

997
01:07:00,567 --> 01:07:05,277
<i>I cannot rule on this.</i>
<i>The police and I are withdrawing.</i>

998
01:07:05,447 --> 01:07:09,326
<i>This judge ordered</i>
<i>the state police to withdraw.</i>

999
01:07:09,527 --> 01:07:11,916
<i>The people has won!</i>

1000
01:07:30,247 --> 01:07:33,045
Natural-gas field of Loma de la Lata

1001
01:07:33,767 --> 01:07:36,998
Gas del Estado
was the pride of the Argentineans.

1002
01:07:37,167 --> 01:07:41,046
It was a showpiece
for companies all over the world.

1003
01:07:41,207 --> 01:07:42,322
Why?

1004
01:07:43,887 --> 01:07:46,447
It managed the extraction of gas,

1005
01:07:46,607 --> 01:07:49,280
despite of the remoteness
of the deposits,

1006
01:07:49,447 --> 01:07:51,802
like clockwork.

1007
01:07:51,967 --> 01:07:56,279
Europeans copied it,
and even some North Americans.

1008
01:07:57,927 --> 01:07:59,280
In 50 years of existence,

1009
01:07:59,447 --> 01:08:03,406
it provided natural gas
to 5 million Argentineans,

1010
01:08:03,567 --> 01:08:06,286
whereas in 90 years
of British companies,

1011
01:08:06,447 --> 01:08:09,757
only 300000 Argentineans
got high-priced imported gas.

1012
01:08:11,127 --> 01:08:14,881
The Petrobras company
estimated that Gas del Estado

1013
01:08:15,047 --> 01:08:17,083
was worth 25 billion dollars.

1014
01:08:17,607 --> 01:08:21,316
After being appraised
by international consultants,

1015
01:08:21,807 --> 01:08:24,924
it was sold
for 2,5 billion dollars.

1016
01:08:25,087 --> 01:08:27,157
- Ten times less?
- Precisely.

1017
01:08:30,167 --> 01:08:34,683
<i>Repsol polluted the area</i>
<i>to such an extent</i>

1018
01:08:34,847 --> 01:08:36,360
<i>that the Mapuche Indians</i>

1019
01:08:36,527 --> 01:08:40,156
<i>lodged a complaint</i>
<i>with international organizations.</i>

1020
01:08:41,607 --> 01:08:44,838
Here, a member of our community

1021
01:08:45,047 --> 01:08:46,605
built a home

1022
01:08:46,767 --> 01:08:48,803
but couldn't move in.

1023
01:08:48,967 --> 01:08:52,084
When he dug a well to pump water,

1024
01:08:52,247 --> 01:08:54,681
he realized that in fact,

1025
01:08:55,087 --> 01:08:57,078
it was gasoline

1026
01:08:57,247 --> 01:08:59,317
that was coming out.

1027
01:08:59,927 --> 01:09:01,679
This is the pipe...

1028
01:09:02,607 --> 01:09:06,202
installed by my father in 1995,

1029
01:09:06,687 --> 01:09:09,759
so he could pump water to drink

1030
01:09:11,487 --> 01:09:13,205
and irrigate.

1031
01:09:13,367 --> 01:09:15,835
You'll see what he got...

1032
01:09:16,687 --> 01:09:18,643
It's gasoline.

1033
01:09:18,927 --> 01:09:20,155
I'll show you,

1034
01:09:21,847 --> 01:09:24,486
It's pure gasoline.

1035
01:09:26,487 --> 01:09:29,047
Seven years ago, supposedly,

1036
01:09:29,207 --> 01:09:31,675
Repsol decontaminated this area.

1037
01:09:31,847 --> 01:09:35,999
What you pump out
is almost hi-octane gas.

1038
01:09:43,967 --> 01:09:45,923
Not only on these 55 hectares.

1039
01:09:46,087 --> 01:09:48,885
The whole ground water
is contaminated,

1040
01:09:49,127 --> 01:09:50,560
to the very bottom...

1041
01:09:50,727 --> 01:09:54,163
Where the ground water begins.

1042
01:09:55,127 --> 01:09:58,881
CORPORATISM
AND MAFIOCRACY

1043
01:10:03,007 --> 01:10:04,565
<i>Menem concludes a pact</i>

1044
01:10:04,767 --> 01:10:07,042
<i>with Alfonsín for his re-election,</i>

