01:10:07,207 --> 01:10:09,323
<i>in exchange</i>
<i>for a constitutional reform</i>

1046
01:10:09,487 --> 01:10:12,081
<i>that includes new statutes</i>

1047
01:10:12,367 --> 01:10:14,642
<i>and an extra senator</i>

1048
01:10:15,007 --> 01:10:16,804
<i>for the Radical party.</i>

1049
01:10:18,887 --> 01:10:20,639
<i>The "Olivos Pact",</i>

1050
01:10:20,847 --> 01:10:22,963
<i>or bi-party pact,</i>

1051
01:10:23,127 --> 01:10:26,039
<i>is signed</i>
<i>without consultations or debate,</i>

1052
01:10:26,207 --> 01:10:28,482
<i>behind the backs of the citizens,</i>

1053
01:10:28,647 --> 01:10:31,639
<i>in order to guarantee</i>
<i>the continuity of the model.</i>

1054
01:10:35,407 --> 01:10:38,205
<i>This reform legitimizes Menem,</i>

1055
01:10:38,367 --> 01:10:42,406
<i>who has enacted</i>
<i>more than 300 decree-laws,</i>

1056
01:10:43,047 --> 01:10:46,278
<i>ten times more</i>
<i>than in Argentina's whole history.</i>

1057
01:10:49,287 --> 01:10:53,439
<i>The parties</i>
<i>have nothing left to propose.</i>

1058
01:10:53,687 --> 01:10:56,440
<i>Radicalism and neo-Peronism</i>

1059
01:10:56,647 --> 01:10:59,115
<i>are emptied of their substance.</i>

1060
01:10:59,967 --> 01:11:02,242
<i>They become organizations</i>

1061
01:11:02,487 --> 01:11:05,285
<i>for doling out public appointments:</i>

1062
01:11:06,847 --> 01:11:09,725
<i>A corporation of professionals</i>

1063
01:11:10,127 --> 01:11:12,243
<i>without any ideology</i>

1064
01:11:12,407 --> 01:11:17,037
<i>that infects nearly</i>
<i>all political parties,</i>

1065
01:11:18,287 --> 01:11:22,326
<i>whose only loyalty</i>
<i>is to their own privileges.</i>

1066
01:11:34,207 --> 01:11:38,519
<i>The once-powerful</i>
<i>CGT workers union</i>

1067
01:11:38,927 --> 01:11:42,124
<i>is now a ghost of its former self.</i>

1068
01:11:42,687 --> 01:11:45,360
<i>Its zealous association with Menem</i>

1069
01:11:45,527 --> 01:11:48,599
<i>finally drove the workers away.</i>

1070
01:12:06,487 --> 01:12:08,557
<i>As they hugged each other,</i>

1071
01:12:09,087 --> 01:12:11,681
<i>the union bigwigs</i>

1072
01:12:12,807 --> 01:12:15,002
<i>betrayed the workers</i>

1073
01:12:15,527 --> 01:12:18,087
<i>and amassed private wealth.</i>

1074
01:12:33,047 --> 01:12:35,481
The Supreme Court

1075
01:12:39,367 --> 01:12:42,040
The court of impunity

1076
01:12:45,207 --> 01:12:49,246
No court was as criticized
and challenged

1077
01:12:49,967 --> 01:12:54,358
as the Menem era court

1078
01:13:28,047 --> 01:13:31,403
Argentinean society faults
the Supreme Court

1079
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:34,360
for its role in a mafioso pact
of impunity

1080
01:13:34,527 --> 01:13:38,406
set up in the country in the 1990s.

1081
01:13:38,567 --> 01:13:42,276
It is blamed
for authorizing and legalizing

1082
01:13:42,447 --> 01:13:45,359
the sale of State-owned corporations

1083
01:13:45,527 --> 01:13:47,518
at odious prices,

1084
01:13:47,687 --> 01:13:50,997
stripping pensioners
of their rights,

1085
01:13:51,167 --> 01:13:54,079
stripping workers of their rights,

1086
01:13:54,247 --> 01:13:59,367
and finally
for exonerating politicians

1087
01:13:59,527 --> 01:14:02,644
who committed offenses
while in public office.

1088
01:14:04,847 --> 01:14:06,838
<i>For dozens of years,</i>

1089
01:14:07,567 --> 01:14:12,038
<i>no important bureaucrat who</i>
<i>committed an offense against the State</i>

1090
01:14:12,647 --> 01:14:14,444
<i>has been sentenced.</i>

1091
01:14:19,047 --> 01:14:21,800
Menem's second term

1092
01:14:26,407 --> 01:14:29,365
<i>Protected by corrupt judges,</i>

1093
01:14:29,567 --> 01:14:34,277
<i>the sinister alliance</i>
<i>of politicians and union-leaders</i>

1094
01:14:34,847 --> 01:14:37,361
<i>with big business,</i>

1095
01:14:38,207 --> 01:14:41,085
<i>consolidates the mafiocracy.</i>

1096
01:14:50,127 --> 01:14:52,766
<i>Gentlemen, it's no easy task</i>

1097
01:14:52,927 --> 01:14:55,646
<i>to lead a country,</i>

1098
01:14:56,207 --> 01:15:00,120
<i>especially in such</i>
<i>hard and complex times,</i>

1099
01:15:00,287 --> 01:15:02,517
<i>where notions like homeland,</i>

1100
01:15:02,687 --> 01:15:05,565
<i>common good, morality,</i>

1101
01:15:05,767 --> 01:15:08,600
<i>respect of others</i>
<i>and social friendship</i>

1102
01:15:08,967 --> 01:15:11,481
<i>are so damaged</i>

1103
01:15:11,647 --> 01:15:13,524
<i>or discredited...</i>

1104
01:15:25,087 --> 01:15:26,156
Eat what?

1105
01:15:26,647 --> 01:15:28,763
I have 7 children, no work...

1106
01:15:30,967 --> 01:15:32,798
I have nothing.

1107
01:15:32,967 --> 01:15:35,322
No mattress, no blanket.

1108
01:15:35,967 --> 01:15:37,958
We're totally indigent.

1109
01:15:49,607 --> 01:15:51,484
Come see my shack.

1110
01:15:52,887 --> 01:15:54,559
Come see it.

1111
01:15:58,887 --> 01:16:00,206
See how I live.

1112
01:16:00,407 --> 01:16:02,921
Everything's wet.
No one helps us.

1113
01:16:03,367 --> 01:16:07,838
They must think we're dogs,
us and our kids.

1114
01:16:08,127 --> 01:16:09,446
I never got help.

1115
01:16:09,607 --> 01:16:13,122
I have no right to anything,
I'm not paid anything.

1116
01:16:13,287 --> 01:16:17,166
I give my youngest some boiled maze
or boiled rice.

1117
01:16:17,327 --> 01:16:19,557
I have nothing, that's the truth.

1118
01:16:19,727 --> 01:16:23,402
I have no way to get another home.

1119
01:16:23,567 --> 01:16:26,957
They promised,
they put down my name, that's all.

1120
01:16:27,127 --> 01:16:29,163
The same as for others.

1121
01:16:29,847 --> 01:16:31,838
Mariela, come see...

1122
01:16:32,087 --> 01:16:35,523
My sister tells me:
"Go to the doctor,

1123
01:16:36,247 --> 01:16:39,398
"you're not well, you're so skinny."

1124
01:16:39,607 --> 01:16:41,643
I can't take it anymore.

1125
01:16:41,807 --> 01:16:44,765
It's intolerable.
There's no work,

1126
01:16:44,927 --> 01:16:48,442
I can't feed my little girl
and that hurts.

1127
01:16:48,967 --> 01:16:52,084
She asks when we're going to eat,

1128
01:16:52,247 --> 01:16:54,044
but there's nothing.

1129
01:16:54,207 --> 01:16:58,166
A child can't understand,
but you have to tell the truth.

1130
01:16:58,367 --> 01:17:02,758
It hurts to have to say
I have nothing, but it's true.

1131
01:17:04,167 --> 01:17:07,682
MAFIOCRACY

